    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-05-10T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-05-10T14:00:00-05:00" n="298"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/2135: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-10T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >May 10, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received May 10—3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>18. For the President from Myron Taylor. In view of changed conditions the
                    meeting of Intergovernmental Committee suggested in my telegram yesterday<note
                        n="62" xml:id="d298fn62">Not found in Department files.</note> may be
                    impracticable therefore will await on events before taking further action.<note
                        n="63" xml:id="d298fn63">There was some further discussion as to time and
                        place for a meeting but apparently no meeting was held in 1940.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
